On Tuesday, August 30, 2005, at 12:53PM, Chris M. <busbodger(-at-)earthlink.net> wrote:

>I've got a 2.0 engine in my Beetle and am considering putting 1800cc heads (I think they have the bigger valves of the 1.7/1.8/2.0 heads). 

1.7L: 39x33mm
1.8L: 41x34mm
2.0L: 37.5x33mm

I've rounded the exact values.

>Wondering if it was worth the trouble (head scratching, boring the heads to accept the 2.0 jugs, thinking further about the cam, heads, exhaust mix). 

I believe the 1.8L and 2.0L heads have the same 105mm opening so you'll  be able to bolt on the 1.8L head to your 2.0L P&C without any machining.

